{"lemma":"كَيِّس","slug":"كَيِّس","root":"ك.#.س","root_slug":"ك-_-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-س","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37401","n37402","n37403","n43170"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%90%D9%91%D8%B3"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bag, sack"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"purse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"scrotum"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"cunning, acute, sharp-witted, shrewd"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to render clever, to make sharp in intellect"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَاسَ (kāsa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic כִּיסָא (kīsā, “sack; purse”); from Akkadian 𒋢𒃻𒉌𒌓 (kīsum, “leather bag for weights and silver”); cognates with Classical Syriac ܟܺܝܣܳܐ (kīsā) and Hebrew כִּיס (kis)."},"ipa":["/kiːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37401","headword_ar":"كَيْسٌ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1:       -A2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isN","text_ar":"كَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37402","headword_ar":"كِيسٌ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A purse;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a well known receptacle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing made of pieces of rag sewed together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for money,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and for pearls and sapphires:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [so called] because it comprises them: (K, TA:) [a remark that seems to indicate a signification of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsa","text_ar":"كَاسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or some other word from the same root which I do not find elsewhere pointed out: but the more probable derivation is from the Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaho","text_ar":"كِيسَهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] that which is tied up, of leather, and of pieces of rag, is not called thus, but is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xariyTapN","text_ar":"خَرِيطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyaAsN","text_ar":"اَكْيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyasapN","text_ar":"كِيَسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (TA,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"membrane that encloses a child in the womb;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$iymapN","text_ar":"مَشِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also, (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scrotum."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n37403","headword_ar":"كَيِّسٌ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosN","text_ar":"كَيْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hiy~inN","text_ar":"هِيِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayonN","text_ar":"هَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Acute,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick, in intellect; clever; ingenious; skilful; knowing; intelligent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K, TA:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isapN","text_ar":"كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaY","text_ar":"كِيسَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a woman, is syn with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isapN","text_ar":"كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and is, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", [each originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuyosaY","text_ar":"كُيْسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyasu","text_ar":"اَكْيَسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) [whence it appears that this last word is accord. to J syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isN","text_ar":"كَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., a simple epithet, like its contr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaqu","text_ar":"اَحْمَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but it has another signification, for which see below:] or, accord. to Kr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysaY","text_ar":"كِيسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isapN","text_ar":"كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and there are no similar instances except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DiyqaY","text_ar":"ضِيقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuwqaY","text_ar":"ضُوقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Day~iqapN","text_ar":"ضَيِّقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwbaY","text_ar":"طُوبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ibapN","text_ar":"طَيِّبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but ISd holds them to be fems. of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DuwqaY","text_ar":"ضُوقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dyq","text_ar":"ضيق"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isN","text_ar":"كَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyaAsN","text_ar":"اَكْيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayosaYi","text_ar":"كَيْسَىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K, TA [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiysY","text_ar":"كِيسى"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoqaY","text_ar":"حَمْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) having this latter form in order that it may resemble its contr.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoqaY","text_ar":"حَمْقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyaAsN","text_ar":"كِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isapN","text_ar":"كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akaAyiysu","text_ar":"اَكَايِيسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is app. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyaAsN","text_ar":"كِيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ti$~apN","text_ar":"طِشَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] You also say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN kay~isN mukay~asN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ كَيِّسٌ مُكَيَّسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: (S:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acute"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., and]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"described as being so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the attribute of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayos","text_ar":"كَيْس"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascribed to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN mukay~asN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ مُكَيَّسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kay~isN","text_ar":"كَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man known as possessing"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayos","text_ar":"كَيْس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acuteness"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraA^apN kay~isapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَاَةٌ كَيِّسَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman well educated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well bred."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN kay~isu AlfiEol","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ كَيِّسُ الفِعْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man good in action"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY daArFA kay~isapF","text_ar":"بَنَى دَارًا كَيِّسَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He built an elegant house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZariyfapF","text_ar":"ظَرِيفَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [The dim."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuway~isN","text_ar":"كُوَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", more properly"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuyay~isN","text_ar":"كُيَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kiyay~isN","text_ar":"كِيَيِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is much used in the present day as signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Elegant, pretty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n43170","headword_ar":"كَيَِّسٌ","root":"kys","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intelligent; ingenious, clever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K.) [Plur."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuwsaY","text_ar":"كُوسَى"},{"kind":"text","text":":] also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akoyaAsN","text_ar":"اَكْيَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}